entry.title: Cordulephya pygmaea

entry.title: Orthetrum caledonicum
entry.content: I saw this dragonfly tucking into what looks like a fly or bee (looks a bit like a Cuckoo Bee). No females observed.

entry.title: Diplacodes haematodes
entry.content: New species record for Riddells Creek. 2nd & 3rd pic shows yellowish colouring on proximal half of wing - an ID feature for this species. No females seen.

entry.title: Xanthagrion erythroneurum
entry.content: On a winter-wet, summer-dry grassland area, road on one side, rail on the other side, no permanent water in the vicinity. New species record for Riddells Creek.

entry.title: Austroargiolestes icteromelas

entry.title: Ischnura heterosticta heterosticta
entry.content: 2 x blue post-occipital blue spots are a key ID feature. 3rd photo (full size) shows what it is holding with two front legs, and eating, has legs. This observation & 4669 are of the same individual & good for ID.
